---
title: Bavette Steak In Cranberry Shallot Sauce with Garlicky Roasted Potatoes & Green Beans
description: You’re sitting at your desk, 3 p.m. rolls around, and all you can think is, “What the heck am I having for dinner?!” We’ve got your back, and our answer is pretty delicious: you’re having crispy seared pork chops with blistered green beans and garlicky roasted potatoes. Topping things off is a tangy sweet and savory cranberry and caramelized shallot pan sauce (party-in-your-mouth alert!). Plus, it’s ready in about 30 minutes—another clever weeknight dinner idea!
